stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> FREE
    FREE --> REQUESTED: build request
    REQUESTED --> GRANTED: compatible acquire
    REQUESTED --> WAITING: row lock conflict
    REQUESTED --> PENDING: MDL conflict

    GRANTED --> CONVERTING: upgrade request
    CONVERTING --> GRANTED: upgrade granted
    CONVERTING --> WAITING: row upgrade conflict
    CONVERTING --> PENDING: MDL upgrade conflict

    WAITING --> GRANTED: blocker released
    PENDING --> GRANTED: blocker released
    WAITING --> TIMEOUT: deadline reached
    PENDING --> TIMEOUT: deadline reached
    WAITING --> VICTIM: row deadlock detector
    PENDING --> VICTIM: MDL deadlock detector
    WAITING --> KILLED: kill query or session
    PENDING --> KILLED: kill query or session

    GRANTED --> RELEASED: normal release
    TIMEOUT --> CLEANUP_RELEASED: remove pending request
    KILLED --> CLEANUP_RELEASED: cancel wait
    VICTIM --> ROLLBACK_RELEASED: rollback or statement abort

    RELEASED --> FREE
    CLEANUP_RELEASED --> FREE
    ROLLBACK_RELEASED --> FREE
    FREE --> [*]

    note right of WAITING
        Row transaction locks enter ROW_LOCK_GRAPH.
        Caller has released page latch, cursor, buffer fix,
        file latch, and MTR latch before blocking.
    end note

    note right of PENDING
        MDL requests enter MDL_GRAPH.
        Physical latch, mutex, condition, and wait slot
        are diagnostic events only.
    end note
